{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 21:32:08.230055", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission complete.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- localized faulty device(s): host_2_1_1_1\n- root cause selected: host_missing_ip\n\nSuggested next steps I recommend (not submitted, but useful to resolve):\n1. On host_2_1_1_1:\n   - Check DHCP client status (systemd service or dhclient) and logs (/var/log/syslog, journalctl) for lease requests/errors.\n   - Confirm the host's MAC address (ip link show) and verify if the DHCP server recorded any requests for that MAC in dhcpd.leases.\n   - If DHCP client failed, restart it or reconfigure static IP if intended.\n2. On the distribution/access switch and router_dist_2_1:\n   - Verify the access port VLAN membership and port state for host_2_1_1_1; check for port security, isolation, or ACLs blocking DHCP (UDP 67/68).\n   - Confirm DHCP relay/agent settings for the VLAN are correct (if using relay).\n3. On the DHCP server:\n   - Search logs for requests from the host's MAC; ensure no deny/blacklist entries prevent lease assignment.\n4. For other hosts listed with null IPs:\n   - Repeat ip addr checks to determine scope; if many hosts in 10.2.* are affected, consider broader access-layer checks.\n\nIf you want, I can run the suggested follow-up diagnostics and produce remediation steps.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2901, "output_tokens": 309, "total_tokens": 3210, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2816}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
